Several different hashiya by Bajuri; according to our dating scheme, we
                  should privilege the one on Banat Su'ad, because it came closest to 1870
                  (Kastaliya, 1869/1286 -- held by Library of Congress, Utah, Indiana). Other
                  Ḥāshīyah by al-Bājūrī were printed, and a number of them non-Būlāq, such as:
                  https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=inu.30000113018323 ;
                  https://catalog.hathitrust.org/Record/008886241?type%5B%5D=all&lookfor%5B%5D=al-Ba%CC%84ju%CC%84ri%CC%84&ft=ft
                  ;
                  https://catalog.hathitrust.org/Record/001933295?type%5B%5D=all&lookfor%5B%5D=al-Ba%CC%84ju%CC%84ri%CC%84&ft=ft
                  ;
                  https://catalog.hathitrust.org/Record/008919255?type%5B%5D=all&lookfor%5B%5D=al-Ba%CC%84ju%CC%84ri%CC%84&ft=ft
                  ;

There are two books of al-Fashnī, one Castelli, the other Shahin:
                  https://iiif.lib.harvard.edu/manifests/view/drs:428521413$1i ;
